news.title: Shikhar Dhawan buys flat in DLF's The Dahlias for ₹69 crore
news.para: Dhawan has bought a 6,040 square feet apartment in the DLF's latest super-luxury project 'The Dahlias' on Golf Course Raod, Gurugram, the research firm said.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves state housing policy 2025
news.para: As part of the implementation strategy, the cabinet has cleared the formation of a ₹20,000 crore 'Maha Aawas Nidhi' at the state level to finance large-scale housing projects under the new policy framework.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty gets Sebi nod for ₹792 crore IPO
news.para: Amitabh Bachchan, Shah Rukh Khan, Ajay Devgn, Hrithik Roshan, Sara Ali Khan, Ektaa Kapoor, Tiger Shroff, and Rajkumar Rao, all have recently bought small stakes in Sri Lotus Developers.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises ₹2,000 crore debt at 7.21%
news.para: Ritwik Bhattacharjee, chief executive officer, Embassy REIT said, ""We maintain a well-diversified and conservative debt book, and this refinancing positions us well to capitalize on future growth opportunities."

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Conditional waivers granted for residential construction under overhead power lines
news.para: The exemptions were granted by exercising rules 62 and 63 of the Central Electricity Authority (Measures Relating to Safety and Electrical Supply) Regulations 2023 based on the recommendations of a three-member committee set up by state govt.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body releases list of 176 dangerous buildings ahead of monsoon
news.para: The list of buildings has been put up on the KDMC website. The civic body has appealed to occupants of these buildings to vacate them and move to safer places ahead of the monsoon.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body works overtime to send out revised property tax bills
news.para: With the two-month rebate period set to end on May 31, MC has appealed to taxpayers to come in huge numbers to pay their taxes and avail themselves of the rebate on both residential and commercial properties.

news.title: Ranchi smart city plots' auction faces multiple delays
news.para: A total of 60 plots were identified for commercial, institutional, and residential development. Of these, only 16 were auctioned and registered between 2021 and 2024.

news.title: O3plus' managing director buys bungalow in Delhi for ₹72 crore
news.para: According to documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, Kapur has paid Rs 1.8 crore stamp duty for the bunglow that stands on a 663 sq m plot. The transaction was registered in the first week of April.

news.title: Odisha government issues SOP for PMAY 2.0 houses
news.para: The SOP, specifically issued for house allotment in Bhubaneswar, covers critical areas such as eligibility criteria of beneficiaries, the mode of allotment of houses, and the handing over process of the houses, among others.

news.title: Uttarakhand: About 790 illegal colonies identified in Udham Singh Nagar
news.para: In Gadarpur alone, 109 colonies were found to be developed on agricultural land and 13 on non-agricultural land. Jaspur reported 88 such colonies, Bazpur 115, Kashipur 175, Kichha 125, Sitarganj 99, and Rudrapur 66.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh cabinet approves amendments to town planning rules
news.para: In its meeting chaired by Chief Minister Sukhvinder Singh Sukhu, the Cabinet also approved the Pashu Mitra Policy, 2025, under which 1,000 posts of 'pashu mitras (multitask workers)' will be filled in the animal husbandry department.

news.title: DLF's net profit grows 39.39% in Q4 FY25
news.para: DLF's net consolidated total income stood at ₹3,347.77 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 44.51 per cent from ₹2,316.70 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Property investment dips 10.3% year-on-year in China in April 2025
news.para: New home prices stayed the same for a second straight month and have shown no growth since May 2023 as China attempts to lift the real estate sector, once a key driver of the economy, from a prolonged slump.

news.title: YEIDA will power up ₹450 crore tech hub near Noida airport
news.para: A YEIDA official said the cluster's location near the upcoming airport, the Delhi-Mumbai Industrial Corridor and the dedicated freight corridors makes it ideal for attracting both Indian and international companies.

news.title: MahaRERA de-registers nearly 19,000 property brokers amid compliance push
news.para: The move is part of the authority’s ongoing efforts to ensure greater transparency and professionalism in the real estate sector. Of the total de-registered agents, around 2,463 are from Mumbai city, 5,538 from Mumbai suburban areas, 4,303 from Thane, and 3,476 from Pune.

news.title: Raipur: Illegal constructions on 26 acres of government land razed
news.para: During the drive, around 40 illegal pucca and kutcha houses, including several farmhouses, in Sector 11-A of the Kaushalya Mata Vihar Yojana were razed. Authorities also discovered a CCTV camera installed in one of the permanent structures.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Stir after builder fails to hand over common areas in apartment complex
news.para: Residents alleged that although the association of allottees was formed and registered with the competent authority, the developer was not handing over the common areas in the complex and using them for its own purposes.

news.title: Bombay HC upholds society redevelopment despite member's objection
news.para: ​The court stated, "Any attempt made by the appellant to raise such objections without challenging the decisions taken by the general body of the society would unnecessarily delay the redevelopment undertaken by the society."

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government's GCC policy to position Noida, Lucknow, Varanasi as tech hubs
news.para: ​The policy outlines an ambitious plan to generate over 2 lakh high-paying jobs over the next five years, the state government said in a statement.
